.TH OCLOCK 1
.SH NAME
oclock, o/clock \- Omero analog clock interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B oclock
[
.B -d
]
.PP
.B o/clock
[
.B -d
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Oclock
is a program that provides an analog clock for
.IR omero (1).
.I O/clock
is similar, but uses the Octopus implementation of
.IR omero (4)
instead. 
Besides interface replication and destruction, there is no user interaction.
.PP
The interface is shown on the last screen with user activity unless
.B $omerodir
is set to the path of a row or column where to create the interface (relative to
the root of the
.I o/mero
file system).
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/oclock.c
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IR omero (1)
.SH BUGS
.I Oclock
must be deprecated in favor of
.IR o/clock .

